{"schema":"paperclaw.academic-tailoring.case.v1","case_id":"at-001-uav-small-object-lightweight","user_input":"杞婚噺鍖栨棤浜烘満灏忕洰鏍囨娴?,"supplied_materials":[],"intent":{"challenge":"small_objects","explicit_goal":"lightweight","scene":"uav_aerial","task":"object_detection"},"unknowns":["dataset","deployment_device","accuracy_latency_priority","baseline"],"clarification_questions":["鏇村亸鍚戞彁鍗囧皬鐩爣绮惧害銆侀檷浣庤绠楅噺锛岃繕鏄袱鑰呭钩琛★紵","鏄惁鏈夋槑纭儴缃茶澶囷紝渚嬪 Jetson銆佹櫘閫?GPU 鎴栧皻鏈‘瀹氾紵"],"baseline_expectation":{"candidate_families":["YOLO nano/tiny family","RTMDet-Tiny","YOLOX-Tiny"],"must_verify":["exact version or commit","VisDrone or selected aerial split","AP_small and latency baseline","TensorRT/ONNX path if Jetson is chosen"],"preferred_role":"A reproducible lightweight one-stage detector with maintained code and deployable export path."},"parallel_expectations":[{"candidate_families":["high-resolution P2/shallow-feature branch","TinyDet-style high-resolution lightweight feature preservation"],"mechanism":"reduce loss of spatial detail for tiny targets","role":"small-object mechanism"},{"candidate_families":["depthwise/PConv/Ghost lightweight fusion","sparse high-resolution computation such as QueryDet-style routing"],"mechanism":"offset the cost of high-resolution processing","role":"efficiency mechanism"},{"candidate_families":["existing YOLO plus P2 aerial detectors"],"mechanism":"detect whether the apparent contribution is already saturated","role":"novelty-risk evidence"}],"hypothesis":"Under aerial small-object conditions, repeated downsampling loses spatial evidence; adding one high-resolution shallow branch should improve AP_small while a lightweight fusion operator keeps latency within the selected device guardrail.","tailoring_advice":{"alternatives":["use sparse regional high-resolution processing only if the P2 pilot violates latency","choose distillation/quantization rather than architecture changes when deployment is the dominant goal"],"recommended_stitch":"Freeze a nano/ti