绱犵骇瑁傜紳鍖哄煙锛岃繕鏄彧鍒ゆ柇鏄惁瀛樺湪瑁傜紳锛?,"鐩爣璁惧鏄墜鏈恒€丣etson锛岃繕鏄叾浠栧祵鍏ュ紡璁惧锛?],"baseline_expectation":{"candidate_families":["MobileNet/ENet/BiSeNet lightweight segmentation","YOLO nano detector when box output is sufficient"],"must_verify":["image resolution and minimum crack scale","edge-device latency","class imbalance handling","data split leakage"],"preferred_role":"A reproducible lightweight segmentation or detection baseline selected only after output type is clarified."},"parallel_expectations":[{"candidate_families":["multi-scale edge-aware decoder","boundary-aware loss"],"mechanism":"preserve elongated low-width structures","role":"thin-structure preservation"},{"candidate_families":["knowledge distillation","structured pruning","INT8 quantization"],"mechanism":"reduce runtime cost without changing task semantics","role":"deployment compression"}],"hypothesis":"For thin cracks, aggressive encoder downsampling removes boundary evidence; an edge-aware lightweight decoder or boundary loss should increase recall/IoU for narrow cracks without exceeding device latency.","tailoring_advice":{"alternatives":["switch to detection if pixel masks are not required","use tiling when crack scale is smaller than the network stride"],"recommended_stitch":"First freeze a lightweight segmentation baseline; add one edge/boundary mechanism, then apply post-training or quantization-aware compression as a separate deployment stage.","reject":["selecting a detector before clarifying output type","comparing different image resolutions without controlling compute"]},"experiment_plan":["E0 baseline","E1 boundary-aware loss only","E2 lightweight decoder only","E3 best single mechanism + compression","report IoU/F1/recall on thin-crack subset plus latency and memory"],"stop_conditions":["Stop if gains occur only from larger input resolution.","Revise if annotations are too coarse for pixel-level claims.","No-go for real-time claims without hardware measurement."],"decision":"REVISE_TO_PILOT","special_assertions":{"required":["distinguish verified, inferred, proposed, and unknown statements","verify supplied-paper identity and role before using it","reject irrelevant retrieval results even when DOI or metadata is valid","bind every core paper to a specific gap, module, comparison, or risk role","produce a minimal pilot before a full combined method"],"forbidden":["fabricate paper identifiers, results, code availability, or reproduced metrics","treat keyword overlap as sufficient evidence","force supplied papers to be compatible","claim novelty from A+B+C composition alone","hide stronger baselines, failed modules, or negative results"]},"tags":["computer_vision","no_supplied_paper","output_ambiguity"],"trace_profile":"academic-tailoring-gold-trace-v1"} {"schema":"paperclaw.academic-tailoring.case.v1","case_id":"at-003-skin-lesion-explainability","user_input":"鍖诲褰卞儚涓殑鐨偆鐥呭彉鍒嗙被鍜屽彲瑙ｉ噴鎬у垎鏋?,"supplied_materials":[],"intent":{"goals":["classification","explainability"],"scene":"dermoscopy","task":"image_classification"},"unknowns":["dataset","binary_vs_multiclass","clinical_claim_scope","class_imbalance_priority"],"clarification_questions":["鍑嗗鍋氳壇鎭舵€т簩鍒嗙被杩樻槸澶氱被鍒梾鍙樺垎绫伙紵","瑙ｉ噴鎬ф槸鐢ㄤ簬妯″瀷瀹℃煡锛岃繕鏄笇鏈涙彁鍑轰复搴婃湁鏁堟€т富寮狅紵"],"baseline_expectation":{"candidate_families":["ResNet","EfficientNet","lightweight ViT when compute permits"],"must_verify":["patient-level split","class distribution","AUC/balanced accuracy","external validation availability"],"preferred_role":"A reproducible CNN/ViT image classifier on a public dermoscopy dataset."},"parallel_expectations":[{"candidate_families":["class-balanced loss","focal loss","sampling with calibration checks"],"mechanism":"reduce majority-class dominance","role":"imbalance mechanism"},{"candidate_families":["Grad-CAM/CAM","concept-based explanation"],"mechanism":"inspect evidence localization without equating heatmaps with causality","role":"explainability mechanism"}],"hypothesis":"Under imbalanced dermoscopy data, standard empirical risk minimization underweights rare lesions; class-balanced optimization should improve macro metrics while post-hoc explanations are used only for auditing, not clinical causality claims.","tailoring_advice":{"alternatives":["calibrated thresholding when deployment cost matters","external-domain validation before clinical wording"],"recommended_stitch":"Use one imbalance intervention on a frozen classifier and a separate explanation audit; do not present Grad-CAM as a mechanism that improves classification unless tested as training supervision.","reject":["attention plus Grad-CAM as two independent novelty modules","clinical effectiveness claims from a single public dataset"]},"experiment_plan":["E0 classifier","E1 class-balanced objective","explanation sanity checks with randomization/occlusion","patient-level cross-validation or fixed split","report macro-F1, balanced accuracy, AUC, calibration, subgroup errors"],"stop_conditions":["Stop clinical claims without external validation.","Revise if class imbalance is not the dominant failure mode.","No-go if leakage exists across patients or augmented duplicates."],"decision":"REVISE_TO_PILOT","special_assertions":{"required":["distinguish verified, inferred, proposed, and unknown statements","verify supplied-paper identity and role before using it","reject irrelevant retrieval results even when DOI or metadata is valid","bind every core paper to a specific gap, module, comparison, or risk role","produce a minimal pilot before a full combined method"],"forbidden":["fabricate paper identifiers, results, code availability, or reproduced metrics","treat keyword overlap as sufficient evidence","force supplied papers to be compatible","claim novelty from A+B+C composition alone","hide stronger baselines, failed modules, or negative results"]},"tags":["medical_ai","no_supplied_paper","medical_claim_boundary"],"trace_profile":"academic-tailoring-gold-trace-v1"} {"schema":"paperclaw.academic-tailoring.case.v1","case_i