y, robustness to lighting/camera shifts"],"stop_conditions":["Stop if gain is only from test-set tuning.","Revise if annotation type does not support detection claims.","No-go for online deployment without false-alarm and latency evidence."],"decision":"REVISE_TO_PILOT","special_assertions":{"required":["distinguish verified, inferred, proposed, and unknown statements","verify supplied-paper identity and role before using it","reject irrelevant retrieval results even when DOI or metadata is valid","bind every core paper to a specific gap, module, comparison, or risk role","produce a minimal pilot before a full combined method"],"forbidden":["fabricate paper identifiers, results, code availability, or reproduced metrics","treat keyword overlap as sufficient evidence","force supplied papers to be compatible","claim novelty from A+B+C composition alone","hide stronger baselines, failed modules, or negative results"]},"tags":["industrial_ai","no_supplied_paper","task_ambiguity"],"trace_profile":"academic-tailoring-gold-trace-v1"} {"schema":"paperclaw.academic-tailoring.case.v1","case_id":"at-005-remote-sensing-dense-small-objects","user_input":"閬ユ劅鍥惧儚涓殑瀵嗛泦灏忕洰鏍囨娴?,"supplied_materials":[],"intent":{"challenges":["dense","small","possibly_oriented"],"scene":"remote_sensing","task":"object_detection"},"unknowns":["axis_aligned_vs_oriented_boxes","dataset","image_scale","inference_budget"],"clarification_questions":["鐩爣鏄惁鍏锋湁鏄庢樉鏂瑰悜鎬э紝闇€瑕佹棆杞妫€娴嬪悧锛?,"鏇村叧娉ㄦ暣骞呭ぇ鍥剧簿搴︼紝杩樻槸鍙儴缃茬殑鎺ㄧ悊鏁堢巼锛?],"baseline_expectation":{"candidate_families":["oriented detector for DOTA-like data","small-object one-stage detector for axis-aligned data"],"must_verify":["tiling and overlap policy","NMS for dense objects","scale distribution","same image-resolution budget"],"preferred_role":"A reproducible aerial/remote-sensing detector matching box geometry."},"parallel_expectations":[{"candidate_families":["oriented box head","soft/cluster NMS"],"mechanism":"reduce overlap suppression and orientation mismatch","role":"orientation/density mechanism"},{"candidate_families":["high-resolution pyramid","query-based sparse refinement"],"mechanism":"retain tiny-target evidence","role":"small-object mechanism"}],"hypothesis":"Dense remote-sensing objects are lost through coarse features and suppressed by standard NMS; matching the geometry head and density-aware suppression should improve recall at fixed resolution and compute.","tailoring_advice":{"alternatives":["tiling policy optimization as a non-neural baseline","sparse refinement for very large images"],"recommended_stitch":"First choose oriented or axis-aligned baseline correctly; test density-aware suppression separately from high-resolution feature changes.","reject":["calling an oriented detector novel solely because the dataset is aerial","comparing different crop overlap settings as model gains"]},"experiment_plan":["E0 frozen detector and tiling","E1 geometry/density mechanism","E2 high-resolution feature mechanism","E3 interaction","report AP by scale, crowded recall, duplicate detections, end-to-end image latency"],"stop_conditions":["Stop if improvement vanishes with matched tiling/NMS.","Revise if object orientation labels are unavailable.","No-go for efficiency claim without whole-image runtime."],"decision":"REVISE_TO_PILOT","special_assertions":{"required":["distinguish verified, inferred, proposed, and unknown statements","verify supplied-paper identity and role before using it","reject irrelevant retrieval results even when DOI or metadata is valid","bind every core paper to a specific gap, module, comparison, or risk role","produce a minimal pilot before a full combined method"],"forbidden":["fabricate paper identifiers, results, code availability, or reproduced metrics","treat keyword overlap as sufficient evidence","force supplied papers to be compatible","claim novelty from A+B+C composition alone","hide stronger baselines, failed modules, or negative results"]},"tags":["remote_sensing","no_supplied_paper","geometry_ambiguity"],"trace_profile":"academic-tailoring-gold-trace-v1"}